public class Token
extends VAnnotation
A word. A sequence of alpha-numeric characters bounded by space. Tokens can be further classified into white space tokens (to cover the stuff in-between words that provide the structure of a document. There is also need to define tokens punctuation tokens, both to define sentence structure punctuation such as periods, colons, and double quotes, but also to allow for those systems that define a word token that breaks on space and punctuation. Updated by JCasGen Thu Aug 18 18:15:19 EDT 2022 XML source: C:/Users/divitag2/work/softwareRepos/bodyFunction/project/60_03_type-descriptors/target/jcasgen/typesystem.xml
